<p>Today, the canonical repository of the Ruby programming language was moved to Git from Subversion.</p>

<p>The web interface for the new repository is <a href="https://git.ruby-lang.org">https://git.ruby-lang.org</a>, and is provided by cgit. We can keep the commit hash from the contributor on the Ruby repository directly.</p>

<h2>Development policy</h2>

<ul>
  <li>We don’t use a topic branch on cgit.</li>
  <li>The GitHub repository will still be just a mirror. We don’t use the “Merge pull request” feature.</li>
  <li>The ruby_2_4, ruby_2_5, and ruby_2_6 branches will continue to use SVN. We don’t push anything to these branches on cgit.</li>
  <li>Starting with ruby_2_7, we’ll use cgit to develop stable branches.</li>
  <li>We don’t use merge commits.</li>
</ul>

